        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`test1.*` files should be safe to mark N/A with the new runner.\r\n`src/testdir/Makefile` remains relevant for test cleanup and non-standard test files.\r\n\r\n```\r\n# git -C .vim-src ls-files .\\src\\testdir\\Make*.mak\r\nsrc/testdir/Make_all.mak\r\nsrc/testdir/Make_amiga.mak\r\nsrc/testdir/Make_dos.mak\r\nsrc/testdir/Make_ming.mak\r\nsrc/testdir/Make_mvc.mak\r\n````\r\n\r\n```\r\n# git grep '\\.mak' .\\scripts\\\r\nscripts/vim-patch.sh:217:  # Remove gui, setup, screen dumps, testdir/Make_*.mak files\r\nscripts/vim-patch.sh:218:  local na_src_testdir='gui_.*\\|Make_amiga\\.mak\\|Make_dos\\.mak\\|Make_ming\\.mak\\|Make_vms\\.mms\\|dumps/.*\\.dump\\|setup_gui\\.vim'\r\nscripts/vim_na_files.txt:90:src/testdir/Make_amiga.mak\r\nscripts/vim_na_files.txt:91:src/testdir/Make_dos.mak\r\nscripts/vim_na_regexp.txt:32:^runtime/.\\+\\.mak$\r\n```\r\n\r\n`src/testdir/*.mak` files are N/A now.",
